TagHandler classes are specific to Transponder standards like ISO 14443, ISO 15693, ISO 18000-3M3 and EPC Class 1 Gen 2 or customized for manufacturer specific extended API. Each standard and chip type is implemented as a class and all classes together build a hierarchical system of derived classes.

Precondition for the use of TagHandler classes is 1st the use of the methods inventory and select from the Reader class ReaderModule and 2nd the identifiability of the Transponder standard and/or chip type for the accurate creation of TagHandler classes. Unsupported chip types are assigned automatically to the base class TH_Base

For more general information, please refer to the system manual of the Reader and refer to Transponder manuals.
